{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review & reform policing to meet modern needs and support frontline officers",
        "additional_details": "We believe that morale and confidence in leadership is low, and that many officers feel overstretched, under-supported, and caught in outdated systems. We think public trust in policing has fallen due to misconduct cases, and what many see as poor leadership and lack of accountability. Reforms must protect good officers, modernise training, and ensure communities feel safe and heard.\r\n \r\nPolice officers need to know they can rely on their government and their senior police officer leadership to back them.",
        "background": "We ask the Government to launch a review into policing and consider reforms to training, leadership, resourcing, and culture\u2014ensuring police are fit for modern challenges while better supporting frontline officers and restoring public trust.",
